8028. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 34110911
T1  - Hyperprolactinemia in children in the puberty - Personal observations
A1  - Noczynska A. 
Y1  - 2001//
N2  - Background. Among many causes of functional hyperprolactinemia mentioned are policystic ovary syndrome, obesity, stress, insulin and hypoglycemia. A frequently observed reason of hyperprolactinemia is also a prolactinoma-a hypophyseal adenoma from lactotropic cells whitch secrete prolactin. Material and methods. Presented are 12 patients with hyperprolactinemia - 10 girls and 2 boys, 14-17 years of age (x- 16 years). Six patients were treated because of policystic ovary syndrome, two had diabetes type 1 and one of the patients Willi-Prader syndrom. In all the patients evaluated were the levels of TSH, fT3, fT4, FSH, LH, testosterone and estradiole. Performed was MRI of the hypophysis. The level of prolactine was examined in the MTC test. In PCOS patients additional IRI and peptide-C in the oral glucose test and USG of the minor pelvic. Results. In 4 of the 12 patients hypophyseal adenomas were diagnosed, in the remaining functional hyperprolactinemia. All the patients are under pharmacological therapy with positive clinical results. Conclusions. 1. In girls with secondary amenorrhea necessary is a precise diagnostic of hyperprolactinemia. 2. Disturbances of prolactin secretion are in the PCOS syndrome frequently observed.
