8047. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 32182765
T1  - Managing epilepsy in young women
A1  - Betts T. 
Y1  - 2000//
N2  - Managing epilepsy in young women demands that clinicians acknowledge that women have special needs related to the effect that their epilepsy and its treatment can have on their sexuality, their menstrual cycle, their contraceptive needs, their potential fertility and the health of their offspring: plus the effect that their sexuality, menstrual cycles, contraceptive practice and hormonal make up can have on their epilepsy. This review examines current knowledge in these areas and emphasises the need for further research and audit of the outcome of present practice. © 2000 Harcourt Publishers Ltd.
