8161. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase
AN  - 29343254
T1  - Insulin resistance in children
A1  - Shim M.L.
A1  - Geffner M.E. 
Y1  - 1999//
N2  - Advances in our knowledge about insulin action have provided insights into possible mechanisms of insulin resistance. The molecular and genetic bases of insulin resistance are areas of active research. In the clinical arena, insulin resistance has emerged as a familiar concept in many specialties. In pediatrics, it is recognized in association with many common physiological and disease states (i.e., puberty, premature adrenarche, obesity, and diabetes). Early diagnosis of insulin resistance will become more important as therapeutic advances are made in the pediatric population. Insulin resistance in children may prove to be a useful early marker for the development of certain diseases such as polycystic ovary syndrome and cardiovascular disease, and its predictive value needs to be studied further.
