T1  - Insulin action and insulin resistance: Diseases involving defects in insulin receptors, signal transduction, and the glucose transport effector system
A1  - Hunter S.J.
A1  - Garvey W.T. 
Y1  - 1998//
N2  - Insulin resistance is a primary abnormality in the evolution of type 2 diabetes and is associated with Syndrome X, a cluster of risk factors predisposing to cardiovascular disease. In the polycystic ovary syndrome, insulin resistance may lead to hyperandrogenism; troglitazone, an insulin sensitizer, corrects abnormalities in the pituitary/gonadal axis in these patients.
