N2  - Data presented in this study indicate that ovulation can be induced in patients with PCOS using a GnRH analogue combined with hMG in a decreasing dose regimen. Based on the observed decline in functional, medium sized follicles in the late follicular phase, it may be speculated that the risk of ovarian hyperstimulation during gonadotropin induction of ovulation in patients with PCOS can be reduced.
