AN  - 19271079
T1  - Clinical and cytogenetic studies in familial polycystic ovarian disease
A1  - Krishnamurthy D.S.
A1  - Naguib K.K.
A1  - Al-Awadi S.A.
A1  - Sundareshan T.S.
A1  - Al-Othman S.A.
A1  - Hayat A.A.
A1  - Moustafa A.N.
A1  - Diab M.R. 
Y1  - 1989//
N2  - The pathogenesis and aetiology of polycystic ovarian disease has not yet been established unequivocally, though genetic and endocrinological abnormalities have been implicated. In this report three female siblings with polycystic ovaries are described. They had amenorrhoea, obesity, short stature, hirsutism and infertility associated with fra 16q22. The proposita was a mosaic 45,X/46,XX,fra 16q22. Her father and two sisters were also carriers for 16q22. As far as we are aware this is the first report of this unusual cytogenetic finding in polycystic ovarian disease, and the finding may be coincidental. We suggest that chromosome abnormality cannot be excluded as an aetiological factor.
