T1  - The central role of obesity (hyperinsulinemia) in the pathogenesis of the polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - Nestler J.E.
A1  - Clore J.N.
A1  - Blackard W.G. 
Y1  - 1989//
N2  - Insulin resistance and hyperinsulinemia appear to be almost universal features of the polycystic ovary syndrome. We propose that obesity permits full phenotypic expression of the polycystic ovary syndrome in women predisposed to develop this condition by generating an insulin-resistant, and consequently hyperinsulinemic, state. The resultant hyperinsulinemia may produce hyperandrogenism by affecting multiple facets of androgen metabolism.
