N2  - This article serves as a foundation for ovarian sonography through presentation of the normal anatomy of the ovary and an extensive discussion of anatomic and sonographic changes that occur during the normal menstrual cycle. The topics of functional ovarian cysts, including follicular cysts, corpus luteum cysts, and theca lutein cysts are considered in detail, as is polycystic ovary disease. The relationship of these conditions to menstrual cycle dysfunction is stressed.
