T1  - Sonographic diagnosis of cervical teratoma in utero
A1  - Patel R.B.
A1  - Gibson J.Y.
A1  - D'Cruz C.A.
A1  - Burkhalter J.L. 
Y1  - 1982//
N2  - With advances in sonographic equipment and diagnosis, an increasing number of fetal abnormalities are diagnosed prenatally. Among the abnormalities that have been diagnosed are anencephaly, hydrocephaly, myelomeningocele, omphalocele, duodenal atresia, hydrops, ovarian cysts, polycystic kidney disease, and hydronephrosis. Our search of the English language literature revealed one cervical teratoma diagnosed prenatally by B-mode, gray-scale static scanning. We describe a case of cervical teratoma diagnosed in utero, in a 29-week-gestation prima gravida with polyhydramnios, by real-time gray-scale sonography.
