T1  - Insulin and C-peptide levels in obese patients with polycystic ovaries
A1  - Pasquali R.
A1  - Venturoli S.
A1  - Paradis R. 
Y1  - 1982//
N2  - We studied two groups of obese patients, 16 affected by polycystic ovaries (OB-PCO) and 16 with simple obesity (OB), matched for age, relative weight and glucose values during oral glucose tolerance test. OB-PCO patients showed higher basal IRI levels and higher glucose stimulated IRI and CPR serum levels. According to these results, hyperinsulism appears to be a common feature of PCO patients, relatively independent of the presence of obesity. Possible mechanisms are discussed.
