T1  - Aspects of cutaneous androgen-dependent syndromes
A1  - Rook A. 
Y1  - 1980//
N2  - I discuss four main aspects of hair patterns and allow myself a few digressions to introduce related topcis. First, I summarize our knowledge of racial and other genetic influences. Second, I consider changes in hair pattern as components of the androgen-dependent syndrome in the female. Third, I mention some of the newer trends in our knowledge of the endocrine mechanisms controlling hair patterns, and I have a little to say about the possible primary role of psychological factors in some patients with androgen-dependent syndromes.
