T1  - Endocrine properties and clinical application of danazol
A1  - Dmowski W.P. 
Y1  - 1979//
N2  - Danazol is a synthetic steroid with interesting biologic properties. The antigonadotropic effect is a primary function of danazol and is observed at the lowest dose level (4 mg/kg). The androgenic effect is secondary and is evident at a higher dose level (12 mg/kg), leaving a relatively wide safety margin between desirable antigonadotropic and undesirable androgenic effects. Other biologic properties of danazol are demonstrable at higher doses.
