T1  - Partial remission of advanced adenoid cystic carcinoma obtained with adriamycin. A case report with a review of the literature
A1  - Vermeer R.J.
A1  - Pinedo H.M. 
Y1  - 1979//
N2  - Adenoid cystic carcinoma is relatively uncommon and often originates from the salivary glands. Although distant metastases develop rather frequently no satisfactory form of therapy has been reported. We achieved a partial remission with adriamycin in a patient with advanced metastases of adenoid cystic carcinoma. This case is described, and a short review of the literature, including papers on the treatment of advanced disease, is also given.
