N2  - Clomiphene citrate is used extensively today to induce ovulation in an anovulatory female to improve fertility. It is well known that the incidence of multiple pregnancies, abortions and overstimulation syndrome in clomiphene induced pregnancies is higher than in non-induced pregnancies. Recent publications indicate an association with hydatidiform mole in clomiphene related pregnancies. Two case reports of anencephalic births to mothers who had received clomiphene as an ovulatory stimulus are reviewed.
