T1  - Endometrial adenocarcinoma and the polycystic ovary syndrome
A1  - Wood G.P.
A1  - Boronow R.C. 
Y1  - 1976//
N2  - While endometrial adenocarcinoma is the second most common female genital malignancy, only 4 % of the cases occur in women less than 40 yr of age. The relative rarity of this disease in young women requires that special attention should be given to those who are at high risk. This paper presents 2 case reports of women with polycystic ovarian disease who developed endometrial adenocarcinoma at 24 yr of age. The pathophysiology of polycystic ovarian disease and its relation to the developments of endometrial adenocarcinoma are discussed.
