8774. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 2 of 2
AN  - 4155174
ID  - 4353921 [https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=4353921]
T1  - Clomifen in the treatment of anovulatory women
A1  - Widholm O. 
Y1  - 1973//
N2  - A report is given on 10 yr personal experience of clomifen treatment for female infertility in patients with anovulatory cycles. The present series comprises 72 pregnancies following infertility which had lasted for an average of 3.3 yr. In 62 of these cases a positive result was obtained after three courses of treatment. The most common dosage was 150, 100 and 50 mg daily from the 5th day of menstruation onwards. No complications were noted with this dosage. In 7 cases ovulation was induced by the additional administration of 4500 IU of chorion gonadotropin given at the calculated time of ovulation. There were 2 cases of twins and 3 abortions. The others were normal deliveries. No noticeable side effects of the clomifen treatment were observed in this series, with a 3-5 day treatment with adequate dosages.
