T1  - Ovarian maturation and cyst formation in children
A1  - Polhemus D.W. 
Y1  - 1953//
N2  - A number of ovaries of infants and children have been examined with respect to the degree of follicle growth and the extent of cyst formation. It was found that follicle maturation changes increased with the age of the child, the majority of infants over the age of two months showing follicles of at least one mm. diameter. Cystic ovaries were frequent at all ages, the peak incidence being at the age of 4 months. These changes are discussed and related to current theories of endocrine physiology.
