T1  - The relationship of the CO2 reactivity of cerebral vessels to blood pressure and mean resting blood flow
A1  - Ackerman R.H.
A1  - Zilkha E.
A1  - Bull J.W.D. 
Y1  - 1973//
N2  - Paired cerebral blood flow measurements (Xe133) at two levels of pCO2 in 29 subjects have been used to measure both the specific change and the percent change in flow per millimeter of Hg change in pCO 2 (CO2 reactivity). A positive linear correlation has been demonstrated between mean CO2 reactivity and conductance (the reciprocal of resistance). The data suggest that reactivity may be greater at high blood pressures than at lower pressures when measured at the same conductance but that under physiologic conditions conductance values are generally low for patients with high biuuu pressures and effective CO 2 reactivity is therefore relatively small.
