DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 293145238
T1  - Influence of the Stein Leventhal syndrome on the outcome of pregnancy and the further development of neonates
A1  - Beskrovnaya N.I. 
Y1  - 1972//
N2  - The author presents a clinical analysis of the immediate and remote results in children born of mothers with Stein Leventhal syndrome. The disease had an aggravating effect on the outcome of pregnancy. Even in women giving birth to mature babies nearly a third had had a threatened abortion at some (mostly early) stage of pregnancy. Premature babies were born in 13% and babies of low weight in 12% of cases; a threat of fetal asphyxia occurred in 13%, neonatal asphyxia in 8% and perinatal death in 8.8% of the cases. The malformation rate in the babies was relatively high (9.9%) and was mostly seen in cases with threatened abortion in the early stages of pregnancy. There was also a high morbidity after discharge from the maternity home (15.1%) and also a high mortality in these babies (4.6%).
