8813. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 293152630
T1  - Disturbance of respiration in children with acute respiratory diseases
A1  - Tomilov I.I.
A1  - Sokolova N.Z. 
Y1  - 1972//
N2  - Among 2,187 children with acute respiratory diseases and disturbance of respiration, laryngeal stenosis of a mild grade was found in 58% of the patients, of moderate severity in 31%.,of marked severity in 10% and ultrasevere in 1% of the patients. The incidence of diseases proved to depend on epidemic influenza outbreaks. The more severe cases of illness were seen in children aged under 2 (71%). The incidence of severe forms was greater among cases of late hospitalization. A definite relationship of pCO, and pO2, to the extent of laryngeal stenosis was revealed on examination of the blood gas composition. Severe stenosis was accompanied by respiratory acidosis and hypoxemia (pCO2 - 50.6 52, pO2, - 63.6 3.0). Treatment of patients with respiratory obstruction was directed to control of edema of the area below the laryngeal folds, and to measures against laryngospasm and obstruction of the trachea and bronchi with exudate. crusts and fibrinous pellicles. Tracheotomy was performed in 93 of 132 severely ill patients; 21 of these died. More recently there has been a tendency to perform intubation instead of tracheotomy in some of the patients, and due to this it has been possible to avoid some severe complications associated with tracheotomy.
