T1  - Pelvic pneumography in the diagnosis of endocrine and gynecologic disorders in children
A1  - Lippe B.M.
A1  - Scalley J.R.
A1  - Wong S.L.R. 
Y1  - 1971//
N2  - Diagnosis of disorders of sexual differentiation and development in children is frequently difficult and often requires explanatory laparotomy. Pelvic pneumography is a safe, simple, nonsurgical technique for outlining pelvic anatomy. In 15 patients studied, pneumography established the presence of an ovarian tumor in one of 5 children with precocious puberty, demonstrated absence of a uterus in 2 patients with amenorrhea and in one with multiple anomalies, outlined enlarged ovaries in 2 of 3 suspected cases of the Stein Leventhal syndrome, and demonstrated normal female pelvic structure in a patient with ambiguous external genitals.
