A1  - Mukhin V.N. 
Y1  - 1971//
N2  - A study was made of 285 karyograms in 10 patients with sclerocystic ovaries (Stein Leventhal syndrome). No karyotypic changes were found. The karyotype of the patients was 46,XX. An augmented content of aneuploid cells (11.544) was observed at the expense of autosomes (group E)L Chromatid lesions were rarely found. It is assumed that alteration of the chromosomal set is not an etiologic factor in this syndrome. Proceeding from the development of the syndrome in sisters a supposition is made about the possible hereditary transmission of the disease.
