N2  - When maternal pH, pCOs and base excess were measured during normal parturition, no significant changes were noted until delivery. Immediately after delivery, pH fell and base deficit increased, while pCO, remained the same. This change at delivery was measured in 4 groups of pregnant women: those in elective cesarean section, normal labor, oxytocin enforced labor, and labor with preeclampsia. Significant differences were noted between the values of the cesarean section group and those of the normaland oxytocin labor group. No differences were noted between parturients who had normal labor and those who had labor induced by oxytocin. Patients with preeclampsia had the largest change in pH and base deficit at delivery.
