N2  - The glucocorticoid function of the adrenal cortex was studied in 41 patients with Stein Leventhal syndrome during surgical operations and in the postoperative period. Bilateral wedge resection of the ovaries was performed under endotracheal ether oxygen anesthesia with the use of depolarizing muscle relaxants. Barbiturates were used for preliminary anesthesia. In this group of patients there are 3 response reactions of the adrenal cortex (satisfactory, weak and paradoxical). A reduction of the potential reserves of the adrenal cortex in most cases testifies to a relative functional insufficiency of the adrenal cortex during operations and in the postoperative period.
