N2  - Ovulation was achieved in 26 patients receiving HMG-HCG therapy and pregnancy resulted in 18 cases out of 30 patients. Of 84 treatment cycles, forty-nine were ovulatory. Four twin and one quadruplet gestation as well as 4 early abortions were noted in this series. Best results occurred in women with defective gonadotropin excretion and/or prolonged amenorrhea. Issues concerning selection of patients, side effects, multiple birth, and clinical management of drug administration are discussed.
