T1  - Hereditary factors in the stein-leventhal syndrome
A1  - Cooper H.E.
A1  - Spellacy W.N.
A1  - Prem K.A.
A1  - Cohen W.D. 
Y1  - 1968//
N2  - The authors studied the hereditary factors in 18 families with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. Chromosomal analyses were made for the propositi. Clinical examinations and steroid evaluations were conducted for mothers and sisters of the propositi and for two matched control groups. Culdoscopy was performed on most of those persons showing clinical signs of the syndrome. The results permit the following conclusions: The Stein-Leventhal syndrome has a hereditary basis. A typical and consistent chromosomal abnormality is apparently not associated with the syndrome. The transmission of the hereditary potential for the disease is consistent with a dominant mode of inheritance, probably autosomal. Bilaterally enlarged cystic ovaries with pale, smooth, thickened capsules may not be an essential manifestation of the hereditary potential for the disease, but is probably the best single indication.
