8882. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 288087812
T1  - Hypothalamic factors in gonadotropic hormone regulation
A1  - Ratner A.
A1  - Dhariwal A.P.S.
A1  - McCann S.M. 
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - Evidence has been presented for the existence and physiologic role for hypothalamic factors controlling FSH, LH, and prolactin release. Presumably, these hypothalamic factors constitute a new family of hormonal substances which appear to be of a polypeptide nature. Work is presently being carried-out to determine the actual structure of these factors, and it is hoped that in the near future such detailed structural analysis will eventually lead to chemical synthesis of these factors. Because of the relatively small amounts of these agents in hypothalamic extracts, large-scale clinical trial of these factors must await their synthesis. It is quite likely that these factors will ultimately take their place in the therapeutic armamentarium. For example, LHRF may be capable of evoking ovulation in women with anovulatory syndromes caused by hypothalamic dysfunction. Furthermore, FSHRF and LHRF should prove to be valuable tools in the assessment of pituitary gonadotropin secretory capacity.
