A1  - Tima L. 
Y1  - 1967//
N2  - An amount of 0.5 mg of testosterone propionate (TP) injected directly into the body of fetuses caused both external masculinization and anovulatory ovaries. Five to 16 mg of TP given to pregnant rats in small daily doses during the last 3 to 7 days of pregnancy induced persistent vaginal cornification and anovulatory polyfollicular ovaries in the offspring. The findings show that androgen sterilization can be induced by the administration of TP to rat fetuses or to pregnant mothers. Ovarian hormones injected into newborn males during the critical period of the first 10 days of life prevented the masculinization of the hypothalamopituitary axis occurring normally in the male rat in this period of life.
