N2  - The rebreathing technique of Collier for measuring Pvco has been modified for use in newborn infants. Comparative measurements on newboms within the first 30 hr of life by this modification and by direct blood PCO. The accuracy of the method was not affected by recirculating the analyzed gas into the rebreathing system; however, under these circumstances the sampling rate relative to the equilibration time in the rebreathing system becomes more criticaJ. A consistent relationship of the measured values with age was found, which is further proof of the reliability of the method. Measurement of Pvco, by the rebreathing method can be made in newborn infants with reasonable accuracy, with minimal discomfort, and for a practically unlimited number of times.
