8906. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 286041707
T1  - SUCCESSFUL QUADRUPLETPREGNANCY in a PATIENTTREATED with HUMAN MENOPAUSAL GONADOTROPINS
A1  - Neuwirth R.S.
A1  - Todd W.D.
A1  - Turksoy R.N.
A1  - Van De Wiele R.L. 
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - Case report: 27-year-old nulligravida with 4-year amenorrhea following emotional disturbance had 1 anovulatory period after 2-year amenorrhea, and then several episodes of drug induced withdrawal bleeding. PBI 4.8 ttg%; normal skull X-ray; endometrial biopsy: proliferative endometrium; negative history; weight 85 pounds; height 58 inches; normal pelvis; 17-KS 11.5; 17 -KGS 12; FSH positive at 10, but negative at 50 units. Clomiphene on 3 occasions produced biphasic temperature followed by abnormal menses, and succeeded by recurrent amenorrhea. In January, 1963 Pergonal (25-E38-B. lnst. Farm. Serono) was ineffective. One month later, HCG was also ineffective. She was then given a 2-week course of Pergonal with HCG the last 5 days. Ovulation occurred on the 2nd or 3rd day of this treatment, and pregnancy was confirmed 4 weeks later. Because of bleeding and rapid growth, mole was considered, but ruled out by sequential gonadotrophin determinations. Quadruplets were diagnosed by X-ray 19 weeks following ovulation. Determinations of urinary estriol, estradiol, es t r one, pregnanediol and pregnanetriol were in the normal range for a single pregnancy. Labor at 34 weeks was ineffective although stimulated and delivery was by low flap vertical cesarean section. The placenta weighed 970 g. and was quadramniotic and quad r ichor ionic. Infante and their blood types: child birth wt. sex blood type A 1800 g F ADCE B 1510 .. M O D c e C 1670 .. F ADCe D 1240 .. F ODCe The mother and infants survived, and are in normal health. The authors briefly review concepts involved in the use of these new and powerful therapeutic agents. Eichner - Cleveland, O. (X, 3).
