8907. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 286066025
T1  - Clinical evaluation of acetylcysteine as a mucolytic agent in cystic fibrosis
A1  - Stamm S.J.
A1  - Docter J. 
Y1  - 1965//
N2  - The clinical response of 16 children with cystic fibrosis treated with a new mucolytic acetylcysteine aerosol is presented. Pulmonary function, evaluated by vital capacity, blood pH, PCO, and O2 saturation, was used as an index for checking the benefit of the therapy. The most severe group, having only a short and initial response, showed no significant change in their disease process. In the other groups, a more hopeful maintenance of pulmonary status was demonstrated. Acetylcysteine appears to be a useful mucolytic agent in the treatment of cystic fibrosis, and deserves further clinical trial and evaluation.
