8921. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 281120123
T1  - Diffusion impairment in obstructive pulmonary emphysema
A1  - Lim T.P.K. 
Y1  - 1964//
N2  - Pulmonary diffusion capacity was determined by Filley's steady-state method in 62 selected emphysema patients in conjunction with the lung function test and blood gas analysis. It was demonstrated that carbon monoxide uptake and diffusion capacity were significantly reduced in proportion to the enlargement of the residual volume, the reduction often being evident prior to blood gas disturbance. A further analysis of the diffusion data in relation to arterial oxygen saturation and physiological dead space showed only borderline or no correlation, indicating a relatively insignificant influence of ventilation-perfusion disturbance on the diffusion process. The theoretical objection to substituting arterial pCO2 for alveolar pCOa in the derivation of alveolar pCO was examined on the basis of the experimental data. The result indicated that (a) this objection is not applicable in early emphysema, in which there is little blood gas disturbance; and (b) even in advanced emphysema, in which there is an arterial to alveolar carbon dioxide gradient, the error is sufficiently small to refute the objection in clinical application.
