N2  - The oestrogen level was estimated by cytohormonal analysis using Schmitt's classification, by Mack and Ale's glycogen test, by the rate of crystallization of the cervical mucus and by histological examination of the endometrium in 22 patients with carcinoma of the cervix uteri. The results showed that 16 of the patients had an anovulatory cycle and that the majority had a high oestrogen content. One should not conclude that hyperoestrogenism by itself is the principal cause of carcinomatous change in the cervix, but it certainly is one of the predisposing factors.
