8932. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 280887201
T1  - Psychogbnjc factors in anovulatory women. ui. behavioral and psychoanalytic aspects of anovulatory amenorrhea
A1  - Loftus T.A. 
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - Five anovulatory, araenorrhoeic young women have responded to psychotherapy with favourable hormonal changes as measured by gonadotrophins and urinary oestrogen levels and vaginal smears. Four of the 5 responded with spontaneous menstruation. In 2 cases, cycling was demonstrated by biphasic basal temperature and excretion of pregnanediol on days 19 and 22, respectively. One case (no. 3) has not yet responded by menstruation. A common psychodynamic pattern developed, which can be summarized ab a lack of healthy inatei ual identification, owing to a guilt-inducing, r age-evoking mother, despite the patient's external traits of feminine identification. The emotional life is characterized by a superficial calm made possible by the development of strong obsessive controls over the enraged fantasies initially directed toward the mother. It is equally clear from the standpoint of classic psychiatric diagnostic entities that this syndrome of anovulatory amenorrhoea is not characteristic of any one diagnostic category, but we have found a behavioural common denominator in the psychodynamic and emotional areas as described above, which suggests a functional relationship between anovulatory amenorrhoea and the psychodynamic and emotional factors described. When psychotherapy has been successful it has progressed along standard psychoanalytically oriented lines. There is as yet no evidence that any other type of psychiatric therapy such as drugs or convulsive therapy would be effective. In this preliminary series, one childish, dependent woman, (case 3) responded minimally (although positively), leading one to suspect that resistance to ovulation may parallel resistance to change in the basic personality. It is the author's opinion that the patient should continue in psychotherapy until the normal pattern has been established for several months.
