8941. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 281453152
T1  - Effect of dehydroepiandrosterone and delta4-androstenedione on the reproductive organs of female rats: Production of cystic changes in the ovary
A1  - Roy S.
A1  - Mahesh V.B.
A1  - Greenblatt R.B. 
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - A study of the effect of dehydroepiandrosterone (DHA) and DELTA4-androstenedione on the reproductive organs of young female rats was undertaken to ascertain whether cystic changes in the ovary can be induced by these androgens. Rats were treated with graded doses of the androgens from 0.1 to 30 mg./kg. body weight for 36 days. The ana-bolic action of the androgens was noted in the greater gain in body weight of treated rats over controls. Both androgens produced decreased relative weights of the ovaries, with the DHA-treated rats exhibiting these changes at lower dosages. At the higher dose levels, both compounds produced cystic changes in the ovaries of most of the animals and increased uterine weights of the recipients. The uterotrophic effect was also demonstrated with median dosages of DELTA4-androstenedione. Decreased adrenal weight was observed with higher dosages of both steroids. A hypothesis for the pathogenesis of the polycystic ovary syndrome is presented, relating such changes to a possible ovarian production of androgens due to an enzymatic abnormality blocking oestrogen biosynthesis.
