A1  - Dorino G.K.I. 
Y1  - 1962//
N2  - A report is given of a normal pregnancy terminating with delivery of a healthy child which remained alive. The mother was a normally developed girl of 12 yr. of age who had not menstruated before pregnancy occurred. According to the literature and personal studies, Von Mickulicz-Radecki and Kausch (1935) were correct in postulating that conception during the first, or the first two, years after menarche is rare, since in this period the great majority of cycles is either anovulatory or the corpus luteum phase is considerably shortened, so that sterility is the consequence.
