T1  - Acidosis following respiratory alkalosis in thoracic operations with and without heart-lung bypass
A1  - Dobell A.R.C.
A1  - Gutelius J.R.
A1  - Murphy D.R. 
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - A group of 22 children operated on with bypass was compared with a group of 8 children operated on without bypass, so far as their pCO2, blood pH and plasma bicarbonate were concerned. In both groups during operation an almost identical fall in pCO., and plasma bicarbonate concentrations was found. At the same time, in both groups a fairly marked fall in pH took place after resumption of spontaneous breathing. In both groups the plasma bicarbonate concentration appeared to remain low for a fairly long period of time. Several reasons are given to explain the fact that the alkali reserve remained low. The low pH in the 2 groups did not lead to serious disorders.
