8956. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 281267491
T1  - Infertility with acromegaly andcystic ovaries
A1  - Finkler R.S. 
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - Because the acidophilic, hype !functioning pituitary tumour of acromegaly develops after age 30 in the majority of cases, many of these patients have raised children before the onset of-the disease. Pregnancy after the onset of acromegaly has been reported only 35 times in the world literature. The amenorrhoea and sterility associated with acromegaly are due to pathological changes in the ovaries induced initially by oversecretion and later by depression of pituitary gonadotrophins. Albright found that acromegalic patients with normal levels of FSH secretion could conceive and carry the pregnancy to term. The author presents case reports of 3 female patients ranging from 18-32 yr. of age who presented typical symptoms of acromegaly, with amenorrhoea, headaches, hypertrichosis, sterility, and bilateral cystic ovaries. One patient conceived three years after radiation therapy to the pituitary. She was delivered of a normal male child at term.
