8962. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 280989637
T1  - Stein-Leventhal syndrome with associated adenocarcinoma of the endometrium. Report of a case in a 22-year-old woman
A1  - Andrews W.C.
A1  - Andrews M.C. 
Y1  - 1960//
N2  - The frequency endometrial carcinoma subsequent to endometrial hyperplasia or coexisting with a granulosa cell tumour suggests a possible causal relationship of unphysiological oestrogen stimulation to endometrial carcinoma. A condition in which prolonged unopposed oestrogen stimulation is present is the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. A review of the literature reveals 29 cases of endometrial carcinoma in conjunction with Stein-Leventhal syndrome and in young women with endometrial carcinoma this syndrome was present in 19-25% of the cases. The authors report another case of endometrial carcinoma in a 22-year-old patient with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome. The coexistence of these two entities is suggestive evidence that a widespread endocrine imbalance may be a causal factor in the development of endometrial carcinoma in genetically susceptible individuals.
