A1  - Hellman L.
A1  - Lipsett M.B.
A1  - Pearson O.H.
A1  - West C.D. 
Y1  - 1958//
N2  - A detailed examination of the urinary steroids was made in 13 women with hirsutism, including 4 with associated clinical and pathological findings typical of the polycystic ovary syndrome. Excessive production of 2 adrenal hormone metabolites, androsterone and aetiocholano lone ,was noted in all subjects, together with a lesser but significant elevation in the metabolites of 11-oxygenated hormones. In the light of previous knowledge concerning the source and physiological character of the hormonal precursors of these metabolites, it can be presumed that the steroidal aberration manifest in these women was a relative hypersecretion of androgenie hormone, or hormones, from the adrenal cortex. A significant relationship is strongly implied between the excess production of adrenal androgen and the hypertrichosis in these women. (VI, 3, 10).
