8974. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 280729574
T1  - Polycystic ovaries and amenorrhea (laboratory and clinical observations)
A1  - Haas R.L.
A1  - Riley G.M. 
Y1  - 1955//
N2  - Of 12 patients with the Stein-Leventhal syndrome 7 were treated successfully by bilateral wedge resection of the ovaries. It is claimed that operation can be expected to give satisfactory results in those cases with the following characteristics of the syndrome: (a) acyclic ovarian function, (b) normal excretion levels of pituitary gonadotrophin, (c) oestrogen excretion within normal limits and at relatively constant levels, (d) ovaries questionably or definitely enlarged. Four of the 7 operated women conceived after wedge resection. One of these cases, the patient aged 25, had primary amenorrhoea before operation. The series also included 5 cases with the above-mentioned diagnostic criteria, which were treated conservatively. In 3 cases weight reduction only resulted in normalization of the ovarian function and in one case cyclic stilboestrol treatment gave the same result.
