8975. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 281415555
T1  - Progesterone treatment of anovulatory bleeding
A1  - Holmstrom E.G. 
Y1  - 1954//
N2  - Before 35 years of age a single parenteral injection of 25 to 50 mg, progesterone was given, Regular cyclic bleeding was induced by repeating the injection on the 24th day of succeeding cycles, The schedule was continued until there was evidence of ovulation, Endometrial biopsies were taken, After 35 years of age an injection of 25 mg, was given every 30 days, If bleeding failed to occur after 3 monthly injections it was assumed that the patient was in the menopause, The clinical patients were divided into 3 groups, (1) Primary - no history of previous regular menstrual periods, Thirteen patients ranged in age from 11 to 27, The duration before treatment ranged from 1 to 14 years, The first ovulation after treatment from 1 to 11 months, but one did not respond in 6 months, About half the patients experienced at least one recurrence, (2) Secondary - under 35 years of age, previously regular menstrual periods, Ten ranged in age from 18 to 33, and the duration before treatment from 2 months to 10 years, The first ovulation after treatment was from 1 to 6 months and 3 did not respond, There were recurrences in 3, at 2, 3 and 6 yr, (3) Menopausal - over 35yr, Ln 16 patients the age ranged from 37 to 50 and the duration of treatment from 4 to 39 months.
