8978. 
TY  - JOUR
DB  - Embase Classic <1947 to 1973> Part 1 of 2
AN  - 280561143
T1  - Pigmented interstitial cells showing 'brown degeneration' in the ovaries of old mice
A1  - Deane H.W.
A1  - Fawcett D.W. 
Y1  - 1952//
N2  - In the interstitial tissue of the ovaries of old ce and C57 black mice, cells develop a yellowish-brown pigment which is acetone-insoluble, sudanophilic, Schultz-positive and fluorescent. This pigment appears to be identical with that occurring in brown degeneration of mouse adrenals, and it resembles ceroid. The slight differences in amount and distribution of this pigment in the ovaries of the ce and C57 black mice apparently bear no relation to the relative incidence of ovarian tumours in the 2 strains.
